spanishExample: Esas cosas no valieron la pena.
englishTranslation: Those things weren't worth the trouble.

spanishExample: Vale, contaré el dinero y te daré el vuelto.
englishTranslation: Sure, I’ll count the money and give you the change.

spanishExample: Quiero que mi perra se siente en este banco.
englishTranslation: I want my dog(f) to sit on this bench.

spanishExample: Cuenta el oro y sabe que vale mucho.
englishTranslation: She is counting the gold and she knows it’s worth a lot.

spanishExample: No me gusta el cambio, así que cuéntame qué pasó.
englishTranslation: I don’t like the change, so tell me what happened.

spanishExample: Ella no quiere que él cuente el efectivo.
englishTranslation: She doesn’t want him to count the cash.

spanishExample: Tenía mucha sal, pero valió la pena.
englishTranslation: It had a lot of salt, but it was worth it.

spanishExample: Está contando la mayor parte del dinero.
englishTranslation: She is counting most of the money.

spanishExample: ¡Cuenta todo! Hasta los que son diferentes.
englishTranslation: Count everything! Even the ones that are different.

spanishExample: No contó todos los dólares, entonces no sabe cuánto valen.
englishTranslation: He didn’t count all the dollars, so he doesn’t know how much they are worth.

spanishExample: Yo conté esto, pero ella ya lo había contado.
englishTranslation: I counted this, but she had already counted it.

spanishExample: Valgo mucho y puedes contar conmigo.
englishTranslation: I’m worth a lot and you can count on me.

spanishExample: Cuento las cajas y valen mucho.
englishTranslation: I’m counting the boxes and they are worth a lot.

spanishExample: Tienes que ir a la puerta trasera, la próxima.
englishTranslation: You have to go to the back door, the next one.

spanishExample: Vales mucho y sé que puedo contar contigo.
englishTranslation: You’re worth a lot and I know I can count on you.

spanishExample: Esta silla vale mucho dinero, pero yo no creo que valga la pena.
englishTranslation: This chair is worth a lot of money, but I don’t think it’s worth it.

spanishExample: Si cuentas una historia, cuenta una verdadera.
englishTranslation: If you tell a story, tell a true one.

spanishExample: Cuente la siguiente historia, por favor.
englishTranslation: (Formal) Tell the following story, please.

spanishExample: Este traje valía mucho dinero.
englishTranslation: This suit used to be worth a lot of money.

spanishExample: Valemos nuestro propio peso en oro.
englishTranslation: We are worth our own weight in gold.

spanishExample: Vale, él quiere que yo cuente la historia.
englishTranslation: Sure, he wants me to tell the story.

spanishExample: Esto no vale nada.
englishTranslation: This isn’t worth anything.
